<subSubSection lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="372" pageId="0" pageNumber="371" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1612,2032]" pageId="0" pageNumber="371">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1612,1637]" pageId="0" pageNumber="371">Description.</emphasis>
Body yellowish brown. Fore margin of head with 
<number box="[888,930,1612,1636]" pageId="0" pageNumber="371" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1â€“2</number>
dark brown bands between eyes. Pronotum with brown irrorations. Forewing hyaline smoky brown with a brown spot at apex of claval veins. Head slightly broader than pronotum with a few transverse carinae or striations on anterior margin. Vertex short, slightly longer medially than next to eyes; transversely depressed subapically. Ocelli situated on fore margin and a little distant from eyes, with a transverse ridge between ocelli. Face broader than length; antenna longer than half body length, located at front top corner of eye; antennal pit deep and expanded onto frontoclypeus; frontoclypeus with median area slightly swollen; anteclypeus narrowed medially with base broader than apex; lora large. Pronotum with sides short. Scutellum about same length as pronotum. Front femur with anteroventral (AV 
<number box="[1112,1121,1864,1888]" pageId="0" pageNumber="371" value="1.0">1</number>
) setae long, intercalary (IC) row with about 
<number box="[332,360,1900,1924]" pageId="0" pageNumber="371" value="13.0">13</number>
setae; AM 
<number box="[491,500,1900,1924]" pageId="0" pageNumber="371" value="1.0">1</number>
seta large, situated near apex; AV setae absent. Fore tibia with setal formula 
<number box="[1385,1396,1900,1924]" pageId="0" pageNumber="371" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[1415,1432,1900,1924]" pageId="0" pageNumber="371" value="4.0">4</number>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[151,207,1935,1960]" name="India" pageId="0" pageNumber="371">Hind</collectingCountry>
femur apical setal formula 
<number box="[536,552,1936,1960]" pageId="0" pageNumber="371" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[569,585,1936,1960]" pageId="0" pageNumber="371" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[603,613,1936,1960]" pageId="0" pageNumber="371" value="1.0">1</number>
. Forewing with three subapical cells and the first subapical cell open; clavus with crossvein between inner claval vein and claval suture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1612,2032]" lastBlockId="1.[151,1436,151,680]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="372" pageId="0" pageNumber="371">Male genitalia with pygofer side broad basally, tapering to rounded or acute apex, with numerous distal macrosetae. Xth segment with well developed apical process on each side. Subgenital plate long with digitate apex; with short fine setae ventrally and along lateral margin, without macrosetae. Style with apical process short, produced laterally rostriform, with fine sculpture; lateral lobe slight to prominent; outer basal arm robust, inner basal arm short. Connective short, H-shaped with stem shorter than arms. Additional sclerite articulated between connective and aedeagus. Aedeagus with lobed area of dorsal apodeme well developed; shaft simple, cylindrical, evenly curved dorsally or sinuate in lateral view, with pair of apical processes or triangular shaped process on each side apically; gonopore subapical on ventral surface.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,847,404,429]" pageId="1" pageNumber="372" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,151,680]" box="[199,847,404,429]" pageId="1" pageNumber="372">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,404,429]" pageId="1" pageNumber="372">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,426,404,429]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="372">China</collectingCountry>
(Henan, Guangxi, Sichuan, Yunnan).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1340,439,464]" pageId="1" pageNumber="372" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,151,680]" box="[199,1340,439,464]" pageId="1" pageNumber="372">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,439,464]" pageId="1" pageNumber="372">Etymology.</emphasis>
The genus name refers to the hooked anal tube and overall similarity to the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1259,1334,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bhatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="372" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1259,1334,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="372">Bhatia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="372" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,151,680]" pageId="1" pageNumber="372">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,476,501]" pageId="1" pageNumber="372">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant" authorityName="Distant" box="[611,779,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bhatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="372" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[611,686,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="372">Bhatia</emphasis>
Distant
</taxonomicName>
based on the additional sclerite articulated between the connective and aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[448,522,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1728,1750]" captionTargetBox="[242,1396,223,1688]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,193,1706]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 Bhatiahamus flabellata A, male, dorsal view; B, head, dorso-anterior view; C, face; D, male, lateral view; E â€“ F, male pygofer, lateral and caudal view respectively; G, valve, subgenital plates and style, ventral view; H â€“ J, aedeagus, lateral view and ventral view; K, apex of aedeagus (enlarged); L, connective; M, additional sclerite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226144/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="372">
Figs. 
<number box="[512,522,512,536]" pageId="1" pageNumber="372" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
M, 
<number box="[566,580,512,536]" pageId="1" pageNumber="372" value="2.0">2</number>
K) but can be distinguished by the character of the anal hook. 
<taxonomicName box="[1288,1436,512,536]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bhatiahamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="371" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1288,1436,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="372">Bhatiahamus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<emphasis box="[271,410,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="372">Roxasellana</emphasis>
Zhang in the shape of the dorsoatrium of the aedeagus but differs in the characteristics of the connective and the additional sclerite (
<figureCitation box="[648,719,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1726,1748]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,235,1695]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2 Bhatiahamus sinuatus sp. nov. A, male, dorsal view; B, head, dorso-anterior view; C, face; D, male, lateral view; E, male pygofer, lateral view; F, anal hook, lateral view; G, fore femur, anterior view; H, aedeagus, ventral view; I, aedeagus and connective, lateral view; J, style, ventral view; K, connective and additional sclerite, ventral view; L, male pygofer, caudal view; M, valve, subgenital plates and style, ventral view; N, forewing; O, hindwing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226145/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="372">
Fig. 
<number box="[704,719,584,608]" pageId="1" pageNumber="372" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
K). 
<taxonomicName box="[765,913,584,608]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bhatiahamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="371" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[765,913,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="372">Bhatiahamus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also similar to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Walker" authorityName="Walker" box="[1252,1403,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Isaca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="372" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1252,1313,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="372">Isaca</emphasis>
Walker
</taxonomicName>
in having an anal tube process, but can differs in having a pair of anal hooks in the former (
<figureCitation box="[1139,1211,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1728,1750]" captionTargetBox="[242,1396,223,1688]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,193,1706]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 Bhatiahamus flabellata A, male, dorsal view; B, head, dorso-anterior view; C, face; D, male, lateral view; E â€“ F, male pygofer, lateral and caudal view respectively; G, valve, subgenital plates and style, ventral view; H â€“ J, aedeagus, lateral view and ventral view; K, apex of aedeagus (enlarged); L, connective; M, additional sclerite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226144/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="372">
Figs. 
<number box="[1201,1211,620,644]" pageId="1" pageNumber="372" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
F, 
<number box="[1243,1258,620,644]" pageId="1" pageNumber="372" value="2.0">2</number>
L), rather than a single process as in the latter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
